FuncDef:
The nat log user keepalive interval command sets the interval at which Keepalive logs are sent.
The undo nat log user keepalive interval command deletes the interval at which Keepalive logs are sent.
The default interval at which Keepalive logs are sent is 24 hours.
CLIs: undo nat log user keepalive interval <interval-num>

ParaDef.Info:
Sets the interval for sending Keepalive logs for NAT users.
The value is an integer ranging from 12 to 100, in hours.

Examples: [~HUAWEI] nat log user keepalive enable syslog type3
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To set the interval at which Keepalive logs are sent, run the nat log user keepalive interval command. The default value is 24 hours.
Prerequisites
The NAT user keepalive log function has been enabled using the nat log user keepalive enable syslog type3 command.
Precautions
The nat log user keepalive interval command takes effect only on the VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E.
